---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<Layout
  title="Our History"
  description="The complete history of Loprinzi's Gym — from Sicilian immigrants to Portland's strongest family and the world-famous gym that Sam Loprinzi built in 1948."
>

  <!-- Page hero -->
  <div style="background: var(--color-navy); padding: 5rem 1.5rem 4rem; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
    <div style="position: absolute; inset: 0; background: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.01) 0, rgba(255,255,255,0.01) 1px, transparent 0, transparent 50%); background-size: 20px 20px;"></div>
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative; z-index: 1;">
      <p class="section-subtitle" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Est. Portland, Oregon</p>
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 8vw, 5.5rem); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #fff; line-height: 0.95; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        The Definitive<br/><span style="color: var(--color-gold);">History</span>
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: rgba(245,240,235,0.75); max-width: 600px; line-height: 1.75;">
        From a Sicilian vegetable cart to Portland's most legendary gym — the complete story of
        the Loprinzi family, their iron, and the institution they built for the love of health.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Red banner -->
  <div class="red-banner">
    "Good Health — Your Most Valuable Possession"
  </div>

  <!-- John Ruskin quote -->
  <section style="background: var(--color-cream-dark); padding: 4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: center;">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="var(--color-gold)" style="opacity: 0.4; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        <path d="M14.017 21v-7.391c0-5.704 3.731-9.57 8.983-10.609l.995 2.151c-2.432.917-3.995 3.638-3.995 5.849h4v10h-9.983zm-14.017 0v-7.391c0-5.704 3.748-9.57 9-10.609l.996 2.151c-2.433.917-3.996 3.638-3.996 5.849h3.983v10h-9.983z"/>
      </svg>
      <blockquote style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 3vw, 1.5rem); font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-navy); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">
        "There is no wealth but life. That country is the richest which nourishes the greatest number of human beings;
        that man is richest, who, having perfected the functions of his own life to the utmost,
        has also the widest helpful influence, over the lives of others."
      </blockquote>
      <footer style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-coral);">
        — John Ruskin
      </footer>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main history content -->
  <section style="padding: 5rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-cream);">
    <div style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 5rem; align-items: start;" class="history-grid">

      <!-- Main column -->
      <div>

        <!-- Origins -->
        <article style="margin-bottom: 4rem;">
          <div class="ornament-divider">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-coral); white-space: nowrap;">Chapter One</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            From Sicily to Portland
          </h2>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            The story begins with <strong>Pasquale "Charles" Loprinzi</strong>, a man who crossed an ocean with little more than
            determination and calluses on his hands. He came from <strong>Trabia, Sicily</strong>, and made his living as a
            vegetable peddler on the streets of Portland — pushing his cart through neighborhoods, selling produce,
            building a life.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            His wife, <strong>Rosa Formosa</strong>, also from Trabia, was taken from the family far too soon. Hospitalized
            with diphtheria which led to dementia, she was committed to the Oregon State Hospital while still in
            her thirties. Charles raised five children largely on his own, with the eldest daughter's help.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            Being in the produce business, Charles nourished his children extraordinarily well. Years later, the
            family would credit the spinach. By 1946, the results were undeniable — the sons and cousins could
            lift <strong>two and a half tons combined</strong>, earning them the title:
          </p>
          <div style="background: var(--color-navy); padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; text-align: center;">
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--color-gold); margin: 0;">
              "The Strongest Family<br/>in America"
            </p>
            <p style="color: rgba(245,240,235,0.6); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-family: var(--font-display); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">
              1946
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- The beginning of the gym -->
        <article style="margin-bottom: 4rem;">
          <div class="ornament-divider">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-coral); white-space: nowrap;">Chapter Two</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            The Spark at the Hippodrome
          </h2>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            Young Joe and Sam Loprinzi witnessed something that changed the trajectory of their lives. They went to
            see <strong>Clevio Massimo</strong> perform his feats of strength at <strong>Portland's Hippodrome Theater</strong>.
            They came home electrified.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            Without money to buy equipment, they improvised. They started building their own weights from
            what they had around them — cement, tin cans, iron pipes.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="vintage-quote">
            "We decided to make some weights out of cement, so we would take some cans and pour cement into them
            and put a pipe in between. We couldn't afford to buy weights in those days."
            <footer style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-warm-gray); margin-top: 0.75rem; font-style: normal;">
              — Joe Loprinzi
            </footer>
          </blockquote>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal);">
            What started next to their garage — friends and neighbors coming to work out in the yard — would
            eventually grow into a legendary institution. Their brother <strong>Gus Loprinzi</strong>, a skilled metal
            worker, welded and fabricated Sam's first professional weight-lifting equipment. (Gus had even been
            slated to compete in boxing at the 1930 Olympics before breaking his jaw.)
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Sam Loprinzi -->
        <article style="margin-bottom: 4rem;">
          <div class="ornament-divider">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-coral); white-space: nowrap;">Chapter Three</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            Sam Loprinzi
          </h2>
          <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-warm-gray); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            January 22, 1913 – 1996
          </p>

          <div style="background: var(--color-cream-dark); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold); padding: 1.5rem 2rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr); gap: 1.5rem;" class="sam-stats">
            <div style="text-align: center;">
              <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--color-navy); margin: 0;">5&apos;6&quot;</p>
              <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-warm-gray); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin: 0.25rem 0 0;">Height</p>
            </div>
            <div style="text-align: center;">
              <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--color-navy); margin: 0;">160 lbs</p>
              <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-warm-gray); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin: 0.25rem 0 0;">Competition Weight</p>
            </div>
            <div style="text-align: center;">
              <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--color-navy); margin: 0;">17&quot;</p>
              <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-warm-gray); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin: 0.25rem 0 0;">Arm (lean at 160 lbs)</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            Sam Loprinzi was, by any measure, extraordinary. He built 17-inch lean arms at 160 pounds — an achievement
            that still draws admiration from bodybuilders today. During World War II, he led a
            <strong>Navy weight-training program</strong>, bringing the discipline of iron to servicemen.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            His competitive career was brilliant. In <strong>1946</strong>, he won <strong>Most Muscular Physique at Mr. America</strong>
            (runner-up overall to Alan Stephan). In <strong>1948</strong>, he won <strong>Mr. Pacific Coast</strong>.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            That same year — 1948 — Sam opened the gym. He converted a house into a workout arena and hung a sign.
            He ran it for nearly 50 years until his death in 1996.
          </p>
          <blockquote style="background: var(--color-navy); padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; border-radius: 2px;">
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.15rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--color-cream); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 1rem;">
              "A gym owner who actually cared about his pupils — who loved them. He was a man of strength
              and muscle but much more than that, a man who left behind a legacy, rich not just in the memory
              of what he accomplished, but even more so of the gracious spirit that he embodied."
            </p>
            <footer style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-gold);">
              — Iron Game History
            </footer>
          </blockquote>
        </article>

        <!-- The Brothers -->
        <article style="margin-bottom: 4rem;">
          <div class="ornament-divider">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-coral); white-space: nowrap;">Chapter Four</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            The Brothers Loprinzi
          </h2>

          <!-- Joe -->
          <div style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem; padding-bottom: 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-cream-dark);">
            <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.5rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--color-navy); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
              Joe Loprinzi
            </h3>
            <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
              Joe Loprinzi went on to become one of Portland's most celebrated fitness figures.
              He became a <strong>highly popular trainer at the Multnomah Athletic Club</strong> — Portland's most
              prestigious athletic institution.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal);">
              His legacy lives on in brick and mortar: <strong>the MAC now has an entire wing dedicated to Joe Loprinzi</strong>.
              The <strong>Joe Loprinzi Scholarship</strong> for scholar athletes at MAC honors his commitment to excellence
              both in athletics and character.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Gus -->
          <div style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem; padding-bottom: 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-cream-dark);">
            <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.5rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--color-navy); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
              Gus Loprinzi
            </h3>
            <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal);">
              The family's craftsman. Gus was a skilled metal worker who <strong>welded and fabricated Sam's first
              weight-lifting equipment</strong> by hand — the very iron that launched the gym. A gifted boxer, Gus
              was slated to represent the United States at the <strong>1930 Olympics</strong> before a broken jaw
              ended that dream.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Phillip -->
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.5rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--color-navy); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
              Phillip Loprinzi
            </h3>
            <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal);">
              The youngest brother carried the family's athletic tradition into academia. A
              <strong>football star at the University of Portland</strong> in the early 1940s, Phillip went on to become
              a <strong>revered faculty member at the University of Portland</strong>, teaching accounting and heading
              the bodybuilding club. He brought strength culture to the classroom.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- The gym through the decades -->
        <article style="margin-bottom: 4rem;">
          <div class="ornament-divider">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-coral); white-space: nowrap;">Chapter Five</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            The Gym Through the Decades
          </h2>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            Sam ran the gym for nearly 50 years. Through every fitness trend, every new machine, every era of
            aerobics and Nautilus and PowerBars — Loprinzi's remained itself. Authentic. Unchanged. Real.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            The gym houses the <strong>world's first mass-produced Nautilus exercise machines</strong> — a piece of fitness
            history that most museums would love to display. Alongside them sit custom-built, hand-made resistance
            machines built by the family themselves, still in daily use.
          </p>

          <!-- Timeline of highlights -->
          <div style="margin: 2.5rem 0;">
            <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-navy); margin-bottom: 2rem;">
              Notable Visitors & Athletes
            </h3>
            <div>
              {[
                { name: "Ken Patera", note: "Olympic Weightlifter — trained here and left his mark on the iron" },
                { name: "Arnold Schwarzenegger", note: "7-time Mr. Olympia — autographed photo still hangs on the wall" },
                { name: "Jesse Ventura", note: "Pro wrestler and future Governor of Minnesota" },
                { name: "Bill Walton", note: "NBA Hall of Fame center for the Portland Trail Blazers" },
                { name: "Lloyd Neal", note: "Portland Trail Blazers center" },
              ].map(person => (
                <div class="timeline-item">
                  <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--color-navy); margin: 0 0 0.25rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em;">{person.name}</h4>
                  <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-warm-gray); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">{person.note}</p>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <div style="background: var(--color-cream-dark); padding: 1.5rem 2rem; border-radius: 2px; margin-top: 2rem;">
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-navy); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
              The Motto, Front and Center
            </p>
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.3rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--color-coral); margin: 0; font-weight: 600;">
              "Good Health — Your Most Valuable Possession"
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-warm-gray); margin: 0.5rem 0 0;">
              This motto has been displayed at the front of Loprinzi's Gym since Sam opened the doors in 1948.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Bob Hill + Present Day -->
        <article>
          <div class="ornament-divider">
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-coral); white-space: nowrap;">Chapter Six</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            Bob Hill & the Living Legacy
          </h2>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            Bob Hill first walked through the doors of Loprinzi's Gym in <strong>1965</strong>. He was a regular for
            nearly five decades before becoming the gym's owner in <strong>2014</strong>.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            His stewardship has been defined by one principle: <strong>preservation</strong>. The gym remains deliberately,
            authentically unchanged. The same equipment. The same character. The same philosophy Sam Loprinzi built
            it on — no contracts, no initiation fees, just a place for people who love to train.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-charcoal);">
            When you step into Loprinzi's today, you are stepping into a living museum of Portland fitness history.
            The iron is real. The sweat is real. The legacy is very much alive.
          </p>

          <div style="background: var(--color-navy); padding: 2.5rem; margin-top: 3rem; text-align: center;">
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-gold); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
              Still Going Strong
            </p>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 3rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
              <div style="text-align: center;">
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 3rem; color: #fff; margin: 0; line-height: 1;">1948</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: rgba(245,240,235,0.5); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin: 0.25rem 0 0;">Opened</p>
              </div>
              <div style="text-align: center;">
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 3rem; color: var(--color-coral); margin: 0; line-height: 1;">75+</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: rgba(245,240,235,0.5); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin: 0.25rem 0 0;">Years Strong</p>
              </div>
              <div style="text-align: center;">
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 3rem; color: #fff; margin: 0; line-height: 1;">$0</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: rgba(245,240,235,0.5); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin: 0.25rem 0 0;">Initiation Fee</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <aside style="position: sticky; top: 84px; align-self: start;">
        <!-- Key dates -->
        <div class="card" style="padding: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; background: var(--color-navy); color: var(--color-cream);">
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-gold); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            Key Dates
          </h3>
          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
            {[
              { year: "1913", event: "Sam Loprinzi born, January 22" },
              { year: "1930", event: "Gus slated for Olympics (boxing)" },
              { year: "1946", event: "\"Strongest Family in America\" title" },
              { year: "1946", event: "Sam wins Most Muscular at Mr. America" },
              { year: "1948", event: "Sam wins Mr. Pacific Coast" },
              { year: "1948", event: "Loprinzi's Gym opens" },
              { year: "1965", event: "Bob Hill first trains at Loprinzi's" },
              { year: "1996", event: "Sam Loprinzi passes away" },
              { year: "2014", event: "Bob Hill purchases the gym" },
            ].map(item => (
              <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start;">
                <span style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-coral); min-width: 40px; flex-shrink: 0; padding-top: 0.1rem;">{item.year}</span>
                <span style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: rgba(245,240,235,0.8); line-height: 1.5;">{item.event}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Sam's achievements -->
        <div class="card" style="padding: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-navy); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            Sam's Achievements
          </h3>
          <ul style="list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;">
            {[
              "Led Navy weight-training program, WWII",
              "Most Muscular Physique — Mr. America 1946",
              "Runner-up, Mr. America 1946 (to Alan Stephan)",
              "Mr. Pacific Coast 1948",
              "50 years as gym owner",
              "17\" lean arms at 160 lbs",
            ].map(achievement => (
              <li style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: flex-start; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-charcoal); line-height: 1.5;">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-coral)" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 0.1rem;">
                  <path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5"/>
                </svg>
                {achievement}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Press teaser -->
        <div class="card" style="padding: 1.75rem; background: var(--color-cream-dark);">
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-navy); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
            In the Press
          </h3>
          <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-warm-gray); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
